Change summary: Update apache web server config httpd-ssl.conf with parameter retry=0 and disablereuse=On    Cause: apache web servers are normally caches the IP address of the application hostname when they bootup and always redirect cthe user connection request to cached IP address. on the other hand the IP address of the application hostname has been renewed sporadically by the ALB. As a result whenever the IP address of the hostname gets renewed, the web server failed to connect to the user of the application as it was still redirecting to the previous IP address.

This change implements critical security patches in development region for the embedded Chromium browser engine within the Citrix Workspace app version 2307. The update addresses three high-severity vulnerabilities (CVE-2023-3079, CVE-2023-3080, CVE-2023-3081) recently identified in the Chromium project. These patches are essential to maintain the security integrity of our Citrix environment and protect against potential exploits.

This change implements critical security patches in production region for the embedded Chromium browser engine within the Citrix Workspace app version 2307. The update addresses three high-severity vulnerabilities (CVE-2023-3079, CVE-2023-3080, CVE-2023-3081) recently identified in the Chromium project. These patches are essential to maintain the security integrity of our Citrix environment and protect against potential exploits.

This change addresses a critical compatibility issue between Microsoft Edge (version 114.0.1823.58 and newer) and the Citrix Workspace Browser Plugin (version 22.9.0.24). Users have reported frequent crashes and inability to launch virtual applications when using the Citrix plugin with Edge. This update aims to resolve these issues by implementing a patch provided by Citrix and adjusting Edge policies. This change is implemented in development region.

This change addresses a critical compatibility issue between Microsoft Edge (version 114.0.1823.58 and newer) and the Citrix Workspace Browser Plugin (version 22.9.0.24). Users have reported frequent crashes and inability to launch virtual applications when using the Citrix plugin with Edge. This update aims to resolve these issues by implementing a patch provided by Citrix and adjusting Edge policies. This also implements  fix for Citrix Workspace browser cookies, particularly in scenarios involving single sign-on (SSO). This change is implemented in production region.

Changes summary: Urgent fix in the subnet in Bluecat, including DHCP scope for critical services. This includes impact in VLAN6 on distribution switches for data center.

This change involves applying Middleware Maintenance Fix PAK MF-2024.08.1 and Code Hotfix CH-5527 to address critical object errors, including null pointer exceptions, memory leaks, and thread synchronization issues.
This change entails implementing Database Patch DB-2024.09.2 and Performance Tuning Script PT-6823 to resolve severe query optimization issues and index fragmentation problems.

Change details: The script in this change will update the 'is_deleted' flag in the TRANSACTION_STATUS table for identified duplicate entries rather than permanently removing them, ensuring data integrity and allowing for potential recovery if needed.

This critical change involves updating the premium calculation engine to comply with new international travel insurance regulations. The update will modify the PREMIUM_CALC_MODULE to incorporate revised risk factors for pandemic-related coverage.

A crucial security patch (SP-2024.08) will be applied to address a recently discovered vulnerability in the CLAIM_PROCESSING_SYSTEM. This update is critical to prevent potential unauthorized access to sensitive policyholder data and claim information.

This change focuses on enhancing the real-time policy issuance functionality. The POLICY_GENERATION_ENGINE will be optimized to reduce response times from an average of 15 seconds to under 5 seconds, significantly improving customer experience and sales conversion rates.

A critical update to the CLAIMS_ADJUDICATION_MODULE will be implemented to incorporate new AI-driven fraud detection algorithms. This change aims to significantly reduce fraudulent claims, potentially saving millions in unwarranted payouts.

This change involves upgrading customer-facing e-commerce application from HAProxy 2.2 to version 2.6 to improve SSL/TLS performance and enable advanced traffic routing capabilities.
